<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,1308,1454]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
A widespread species, known from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[842,959,1348,1374]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Argentina</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1174,1348,1374]" name="Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Chile</collectingCountry>
. The species is very likely typical for springs, although it has been reported from a pond and a glacial stream as well (
<bibRefCitation author="Besch" box="[447,591,1428,1454]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" refString="Besch, W. (1964) Systematik und Verbreitung der sudamerikanischen rheophilen Hydrachnellen. Beitrage zur Neotropischen Fauna, 3, 77 - 194." type="journal article" year="1964">
Besch 
<number box="[528,591,1428,1454]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
